Class FormEditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ComponentImpl
      • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Container
        • net.proteusframework.processes.form.ui.FormEditor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    PropertyChangeListener, Iterable<net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Component>, EventListener, LocaleContextSource, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Component, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ListCellRenderer, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.ParentComponent, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.TableCellRenderer, net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.TreeCellRenderer

    @Configurable
public class FormEditor
extends net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.component.Container
    Form editor. Edits the FormDefinition passed into the constructor. Set a FormEditorConfig for more control over the UI; otherwise, the system uses one from the user's preferences.
    Author:
    Pat Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • isSafeEditMode

        public boolean isSafeEditMode()

        INTERNAL USE

        Determines if we are in safe editing mode. Safe editing mode means that the revision being edited is currently published and non-safe changes should not be allowed. Changes such as label text changes are safe as they don't change the state of the form. Adding or removing an option from a choice extra, for example, is not a safe change.
        Returns:
        true if in safe editing mode, false if changes should not be restricted except by capability.
